The paper deals with digital modulation formats and their performance in wideband fading channels, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses power efficiency and capacity improvements, which are relevant to the Data Structures (cs.DS), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
